ingredientsDesc: Ready to use reagents1. IgE MICROPLATEOne bag containing 12 strips x8 wells, coated with monoclonal (mouse) anti-human IgE. 2. ANTI-IgE-BIOTIN CONJUGATEOne vial (13 ml) of anti-IgE-Biotin conjugate in TRIS buffer, pH 8.1, preservatives and stabilizers.3. Total IgE CALIBRATORS6 Vials, 0.5 ml each. The vials contain human IgE in horse serum with 0.01% of Proclin 300 as preservative. The IgE concentration are: 0-10-50-250-500-1000 KIU/L.4. INCUBATION BUFFEROne vial (18 ml) containing TRIS buffer, pH 8.4, with 0.1% of Tween 20 and 0.005% of Proclin 300 as preservative.5. SAMPLE DILUENTThe vial contains 8 ml of sample diluent consisting of horse serum, with 0.01% of Proclin 300 as preservative.6. HRP-STREPTAVIDIN CONJUGATE(code AHRPS; vial cap: gree) Each vial contains 13 ml of Streptavidin-Peroxidase conjugate in a red colored buffer, pH 5.5 supplemented with 0.001% Proclin300.7.
